16 SECTION 1. BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF MARYLAND,
17 That:
18 (a) In this section, “child care facility” means:
19 (1) a child care center, as defined under § 9.5–401 of the Education Article;
20 (2) a family child care home, as defined under § 9.5–301 of the Education
21 Article; or
22 (3) a large family child care home, as defined under § 9.5–301 of the
23 Education Article.
24 (b) The State Department of Education shall conduct a thorough analysis of the
25 State’s regulatory requirements for child care facilities.
26 (c) (1) In conducting the analysis required under subsection (b) of this section,
27 the Department shall pay particular attention to current regulations that limit the ability
28 of a person to:
29 (i) register a family child care home or a large family child care
30 home;

HOUSE BILL 477 5
1 (ii) receive a license to operate a child care center; or
2 (iii) operate a child care facility in a profitable manner while
3 providing quality, affordable child care.
4 (2) In conducting its analysis, the Department shall, at a minimum,
5 analyze the current regulatory framework governing:
6 (i) the staffing of child care facilities, including the requirements to
7 work in child care and the supervisory requirements for child care staff;
8 (ii) the physical requirements for child care facilities; and
9 (iii) the programs in place to support child care facilities.
10 (3) The Department shall examine the framework that governs the
11 regulation of child care and child care facilities in different states and regions and how they
12 compare to those in the State.
13 (4) For each regulation examined as part of its analysis, the Department
14 shall determine whether the regulation results in or contributes to:
15 (i) a safer environment for children and child care facility
16 employees;
17 (ii) a quality early childhood education; or
18 (iii) a significant impact on the opening or operation of child care
19 facilities.
20 (d) (1) On or before January 1, 2026, the Department shall provide an interim
21 report on the results of its analysis to the Governor and, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the
22 State Government Article, the General Assembly.
23 (2) On or before September 1, 2026, the Department shall issue a final
24 report on the results of its analysis, including any recommended changes to the regulatory
25 framework, to the Governor and, in accordance with § 2–1257 of the State Government
26 Article, the General Assembly.
27 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect July
28 1, 2025.

